Architecture plan for upcoming issues

Project shape
- Vite + React + TypeScript single-page habit tracker.
- App entry is src/main.tsx -> src/App.tsx -> src/router.tsx.
- Persistent client state is centralized in src/stores/habitStore.ts using Zustand localStorage persistence.
- Shared persisted types live in src/types/habit.ts: Habit, CheckIn, DateKey, store schema version.
- Pure date/stat/streak/import-export helpers live under src/utils/ with focused tests.
- UI components live under src/components/; route pages live under src/pages/.

Issue #77: Refine seed check-in patterns for more believable heatmap shapes
- Scope is intentionally narrow: modify only the function body of seedCheckIns(): CheckIn[] in src/stores/seed.ts.
- Preserve all imports and exported symbols, including fill, isWeekday, SEED_HISTORY_DAYS, seedHabits, and seedState.
- Keep the returned array in the required five ...fill(...) entries matching the existing five seed habits and their order.
- The seed data feeds seedState(), which initializes the persisted Zustand store for first-run/demo data. No component, store action, route, or type changes should be needed.
- Tests likely impacted: src/stores/seed.test.ts and any component/e2e snapshots or assertions that assume exact seed check-in counts/streaks. Update only if the new mandated pattern changes expectations.

Design decisions
- Treat seed check-ins as deterministic relative-to-today demo data using existing helpers daysAgo(), iso(), fill(), and isWeekday().
- Avoid schema changes; this is sample data refinement only.
- Preserve local-first architecture and existing localStorage behavior.
- Keep issue implementation isolated to src/stores/seed.ts unless tests require expectation updates.
